problem_performances              ← unique(user_id, problem_id)
problem_bank_items                ← unique(user_id, problem_id)
performance_snapshots             ← unique(user_id, snapshot_date)
registry_versions

==================================================
DOMAIN MODELS (packages/domain)
==================================================

All 17 types from the spec are implemented:

Core:        User, Problem, TestCase, Submission
Session:     DailySession, TimerSession, ActivityEvent, ReviewSchedule
Training:    UserTrainingProfile, TrainingContract, DailyMission, MissionTask
Performance: PerformanceSnapshot, ProblemPerformance, ProblemBankItem
Registry:    ProblemManifest, RegistryVersion, Track, RoadmapPlan

Enums:       Difficulty, Provider, Language, SubmissionStatus, Verdict, ActivityEventType

==================================================
KEY DECISIONS & ASSUMPTIONS
==================================================

- Go 1.25.1 across all go.mod files, go.work, and Dockerfiles
- Module path base: judge-loop/apps/<name> and judge-loop/packages/<name>
- replace directives in each go.mod for local packages; go.work handles workspace-level resolution
- Single-user MVP: no authentication in v1
- Problem statements are NOT stored — metadata only (ProblemManifest)
- local-agent: localhost:7070 only, proxies to api-server:8080
- local-agent uses SQLite (go-sqlite3, CGO) for offline timer state
- judge-worker mounts /var/run/docker.sock to spawn sandbox containers
- Complexity tracking is self-reported (manual input by user), not automated
- Spaced repetition intervals: 1 → 3 → 7 → 14 days
- Pattern score = accepted / attempted; weak if < 0.5 with ≥ 3 attempts

